instead of extracting the response from context twice (even though cheap), do u mind trying out changing ApacheHttpAsyncClientDecorator generic type from HttpContext to HttpResponse, and extracting response from context in TraceContinuedFutureCallback when calling onResponse, e.g.
    public void completed(final T result) {
      HttpResponse response = getResponse(context);
      DECORATE.onResponse(clientSpan, response);
      ...
    }

i think this may be nicer
also, just noticed, then won't need the response != null conditionals above since response != null is already checked prior to calling those methods

